the national whistlers convention began as 
a folksy gettogether but over 17 years it has developed into a 
springboard for those who aspire to 15 seconds of stardom 
all of our whistlers sooner or later get on some kind of a 
show either the johnny carson show or the david letterman show 
said allen de hart founder and director of the competition held in 
louisburg about 30 miles north of raleigh 
about 60 contestants from 20 states ranging in age from 3 to 
88 were competing this weekend for awards including best 
supporting whistler and prize money totaling 2500 
we have more people come from new york than any place de 
hart said its a tremendous amount of fun to watch 
de hart said whistling is an ancient art form 
it was an means of communication probably long before we had 
language i guess the first whistler was probably the first caveman 
who heard a bird he said 
sean lomax the 1989 national whistling champ is a 28yearold 
computer specialist on a submarine based at pearl harbor 
he won last years title by whistling dance boheme from the 
opera carmen and the entertainer from the movie the 
sting lomax will open the contest today with the national anthem 
after todays competition at the franklin county courthouse 
conventiongoers will gather for a street dance there will be arts 
and crafts displays and visits to the national whistlers museum 
established in 1981 
