see the cramped attic where the frank family lived for two years 
before being captured in 1944 and sent to concentration camps 
known to readers of anne franks diary as the annex the 
apartment is entered through a door hidden behind a bookcase 
anne franks house is the most popular historical landmark in 
the netherlands said amsterdam tourist bureau spokesman herman 
ter balkt its no wonder theyre in dire need of more room 
before the nazis invaded the netherlands in 1940 the building 
on the princes canal housed the spice business of anne franks 
father otto the house next door was taken over by the private 
museum foundation to add exhibit space 
