<DOCNO> AP900421-0041 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
the best small community in the united states 
to call home is the san luis obispoatascadero calif area and 
the worst is nampacaldwell idaho according to a newly published 
book 
the rating guide to life in americas small cities ranks all 
219 micropolitan areas for their desirability as alternatives 
to living in the nations large metropolitan centers 
san luis obispos easygoing charm and mild climate 
helped earned it the top ranking 
the town barricades its main thoroughfare allows farmers and 
vendors to sell food and stages a weekly street fair every 
thursday the book noted 
the books author g scott thomas defines micropolitans as 
cities of between 15000 and 50000 people in counties of at least 
40000 population 
the communities cannot be part of regions designated as 
metropolitan areas by the us government as of june 15 1989 most 
suburban communities are disqualified because they are included in 
metropolitan areas 
more than 15 million people live in micropolitan america 
nearly 65 percent of the nations population said thomas 
in 20 states the smaller cities make up 10 percent of the 
population with idaho having the highest proportion at slightly 
more than 35 percent he added 
in a few states the cities included are independent and not 
located in counties 
one city decatur ala which the government designates as a 
metropolitan area is considered a micro by thomas 
the district of columbia and four states hawaii 
massachusetts new jersey and south dakota have no micropolitan 
areas 
the cities were assigned a points in 10 categories climate 
economics education health care housing public safety 
transportation urban proximity sophistication and diversions 
the latter two categories measured things such as voter turnout 
population turnover newspaper readership movie theaters parks 
golf courses restaurants and retail stores 
the maximum possible score was 1000 
the top five micropolitans in rank order are san luis 
obispoatascadero calif corvallis ore fredericksburg va 
fairbanks alaska and wenatchee wash 
the bottom five are minden la gallup nm rio rancho nm 
lumberton nc and nampacaldwell idaho 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

