the walls of john towers downtown office hold 
daily reminders of the cabinet post that escaped the grasp of the 
former senator and arms control negotiator 
both the swords from west point and the photograph of president 
bush with his first nominee to run the pentagon testify to the time 
not too long ago when tower 64 thought he might become secretary 
