towers rejection in march 1989 by his former colleagues capped 
a rancorous period in the brief history of the bush administration 
and the long tradition of senate comity 
charges of womanizing and alcoholism were leveled at the former 
texas senator while republicans were bitter in their accusations 
of democratic partisanship 
more than a year later tower remains on the fringes of defense 
work dividing his time between dallas and washington he serves on 
