vying for parliamentary seats in the republics first multiparty 
elections in 50 years 
in slovenias secondround balloting 14 million people who 
voted on april 8 will elect the state president and 65 remaining 
parliamentary deputies 
under existing law all campaign activities stop a day before 
the elections to give citizens a chance to think about their 
decisions before voting 
slovenia and croatia have liberal judiciaries and media unlike 
yugoslavias largest republic of serbia and they are already 
pushing for closer ties with the west 
if proindependence forces win in both republics they would 
move further away from serbias hardline communist leadership and 
could tear apart the loose federation of six republics and two 
