butchers between 1976 and 1982 many of them allegedly intended as 
political payoffs he was not expected to repay 
ford contends his butcher loans totaled 650000 and all of them 
have been settled 
his codefendants are accountant david crabtree and lawyers 
douglas beaty and karl schledwitz who are charged with helping him 
get and hide butcher payoffs 
the government called 29 witnesses in its case against ford and 
defense and prosecution lawyers filed more than 170 exhibits for 
the jury to review 
