two university of massachusetts 
researchers have been experimenting the past four years with 
inducing bacteria to grow a natural form of plastic that would be 
biodegradable 
biochemist r clinton fuller and robert lenz a polymer 
scientist brew their natural plastics in jars full of fermenting 
bacteria 
these plastics are made by microorganisms and they can be 
digested by microorganisms fuller said 
the scientists work differs sharply from the degradable 
plastics made with cornstarch that have appeared in the past few 
years those bags have come under criticism because they are mostly 
synthetic and do not degrade in landfills 
the pair have reached the point where they can produce small 
amounts of a tough clear rubbery material that is a combination of 
several types of polymers 
polymerization is the science of chaining together simple 
molecules to form a more complex molecule with different physical 
properties 
