countrys defense forces had first purchased the weapons 
he said saturday that the arms shipment included 
rocketpropelled grenade launchers antiaircraft guns and 
automatic rifles 
the weapons were shipped from haifa israel to an antiguan port 
and then shipped to santa marta colombia according to a 
preliminary investigation led by deputy prime minister lester bird 
the prime ministers son 
in february colombian soldiers found 232 israelimade weapons 
during a search of ranches seized from gonzalo rodriguez gacha a 
leader of the medellin drug cartel who was killed in a december gun 
battle with police colombian defense minister oscar botero said 
last week 
the weapons found included assault rifles machine guns 
submachine guns pistols shoulderfired rockets and infrared night 
scopes botero said 
he said authorities have not been determined how the weapons 
wound up with medellin drug traffickers 
bird said it has become evidentthere were irregularities 
and breeches of our customs regulations in handling the arms which 
were transshipped through antigua in april 1989 
on monday bird said that documents were falsified and customs 
procedures ignored to facilitate the passage of the arms shipment 
through antigua 
the mystery over the israeli weapons follows a scandal that 
broke last year concerning the alleged involvement of israeli 
mercenaries in training the private armies of the medellin cartel 
the colombian government has formally charged two israelis yair 
klein and arik afek with complicity with the medellin cartel 
