a small earthquake struck saturday in 
an area hardhit by octobers killer quake but there were no 
immediate reports of damage or injuries 
the temblor which struck at 7 pm measured 35 on the richter 
scale and was centered in the southern end of the loma prieta 
aftershock zone said pat jorgenson a spokeswoman for the us 
geological survey in menlo park 
loma prieta was at the center of the 71magnitude quake that 
struck the san francisco bay area in oct 17 killing 67 people and 
doing 7 billion in property damage 
just yet another of the continuing series of aftershocks 
said jorgenson 
a dispatcher for the watsonville police department said she 
received several calls from residents who wanted to know if theyd 
just felt an earthquake but no one reported damage or injuries 
it was a rolling she said it seemed like it lasted 
forever 
watsonville is 70 miles south of san francisco just inland from 
monterey bay 
a 35magnitude quake is capable of causing slight damage in the 
immediate area 
