<TEXT>
biography written as a book can be more 
comprehensive than biography done as theater which tends to hit 
the high spots but does literally give flesh to the subject 
an example of theatrical biography titled mountain is now 
running at the lucille lortel theater offbroadway in it actor 
len cariou plays the late justice william o douglas 
its a oneman show with a chorus of two heather summerhayes 
and john c vennema become people in douglas life and speak the 
criticisms of conservatives against the liberal who was on the 
supreme court from 1939 to 1980 
in mountain one gets a feel of what was important to the 
man that constitutional rights not be taken from people no matter 
what their race politics or wrongdoing that freedom includes the 
right of privacy and that wilderness areas be protected forever 
from development 
the play by douglas scott makes douglas a fullblooded person 
and is careful to show faults not letting him be right all the 
time 
as the play begins ones heart sinks its stagey and anecdotes 
sound like toocute party pieces the ending isnt satisfactory 
either getting overheated as douglas rails extensively 
but recounted aspects of douglas life pull one into the play 
according to mountain douglas was president roosevelts first 
choice for vice president in 1944 
and cariou is touching acting douglas as a boy and later going 
from washington state to new york by train he states douglas 
convictions compellingly 
the focus wisely isnt on douglas private life his first 
wife is shown as a shy person his second less clearly as 
personable his third and fourth not detailed at all 
john henry davis directed k amp d productions margery klain and 
robert g donnalley jr produced in asociation with lucille lortel 
</TEXT>
