<TEXT>
new york city has become the robbery capital of 
the united states far outdistancing detroit which previously led 
the nation according to recently reported fbi figures compiled by 
the police department 
new yorks rate of robberies in 1989 was 1271 for every 100000 
in population police said detroits figure was 1095 and 
washington dc came in third with 1055 
the total number of robberies in new york last year amounted to 
93377 or one every six minutes an increase of nearly 8 percent 
over the previous year not surprisingly the number of people who 
want guns bulletproof vests and bodyguards also increased 
officials said 
rounding out the top 10 in percapita robberies were baltimore 
1043 new orleans 1013 boston 1011 dallas 928 los angeles 
913 cleveland 743 and san francisco 664 
to compile the rankings the police department used preliminary 
national crime figures for 1989 released by the fbi three weeks 
ago the fbis final official figures are due in august 
in other major crime categories washington was first in murder 
and new york after the greatest number of slayings in its history 
was ninth on a per capita basis police said 
new york city last ranked no 1 for robberies in 1981 when more 
than 107000 were reported said police commissioner lee brown 
police said that during the time the number of robberies 
increased the number of applications for gun permits went to 
6397 up 10 percent for the year if the trend continues the 
number will increase another 15 percent in 1990 
stephen dandrilli a security consultant whose company 
specializes in obtaining gun permits for a fee that can run up to 
4000 said friday that business has gone up 22 percent in the 
past six months 
people come in and tell me ive got to get a permit now im 
not going to wait around and be victimized dandrilli said 
about 15000 nonofficial new york city residents are licensed 
to carry guns along with nearly 12000 retired police officers 
the department said an additional 24000 residents have permits to 
keep guns in their homes or businesses 
dandrilli said that since january his company guardian group 
international has also doubled its sale of bulletproof vests 
customers also are interested in bulletproof versions of street 
clothes like leather jackets raincoats and even furs he said 
