stiner will oversee an estimated 35000 operations troops 
stationed across the country including navy seaairland seal 
commandos army green berets and rangers and the counterterrorist 
delta force the command reports to the joint chiefs of staff and 
the secretary of defense 
the general who will be promoted to fourstar rank replaces 
retiring army gen james j lindsay lindsay ran the command since 
its formation in april 1987 
stiner a 53yearold tennessee native was chief of staff for 
the rapid deployment joint task force at macdill from 19801982 
in october 1988 he took command of the 18th airborne corps and 
fort bragg nc the corps is comprised of the 82nd airborne 
division at bragg the 101st airborne division at fort campbell 
ky and other support elements 
the rapid deployment joint task force at macdill was formed in 
response to the soviet invasion of afghanistan and the iranian 
revolution the small headquarters evolved into us central 
command which is also based at macdill and coordinates military 
activity in the middle east 
stiners latest assignment was commander of the dec 20 invasion 
of panama under the direction of gen maxwell thurman head of the 
us southern command 
