medical reports show leukemia thyroid gland malfunctions 
cancer and anemia are spreading especially among children 
no nationwide figures were available but an unreleased report 
obtained by the associated press shows worsening health problems 
among children in the vetka region 
in 1986 there were five cases of aplastic anemia marked by low 
counts of platelets needed for clotting and of white blood cells to 
fight infection by last year the number was 114 
cases of irondeficiency anemia rose in the same period from 134 
to 341 and cases of swollen thyroid glands doubled from 763 in 
1986 to 1508 in 1989 
debate has begun over what radiation level is safe the 
government contends a person can be exposed safely to 35 rems over 
his life but specialists testified before scherbaks committee 
that the standard does not account for longterm effects of small 
radiation doses 
virtually all american nuclear power plants limit exposure to 5 
rems a year according to the us council for energy awareness an 
industry group 
aside from human costs chernobyl is taking a huge toll on the 
soviet budget 
new chernobyl cleanup estimates are 30 times the original figure 
of 8 billion rubles 13 billion at the official rate of exchange 
scherbak said surveys by the three republics affected indicate the 
cost could reach 250 billion rubles 405 billion in the next 
decade 
in vetka a new communications center and three apartment houses 
are being built for whom 
i asked a party secretary once and he said we must think 
